      "content": "Generally speaking, interactions between antibiotics and statins are monitored because certain drugs can affect how the body processes others. In some cases, clarithromycin can potentially increase the levels of simvastatin in your bloodstream, which may increase side effects. Because the potential for elevation exists, it's treated as a real risk rather than a minor warning. Please wait for professional medical advice before taking them together tonight.",
